      section#management
        h2 Management
        p I believe in working for, and in hiring, people that I can learn from.
        p.
          I believe that the jobs of management include making the organization comprehensible to individuals
          (by making it simpler where possible, and by simplifying its presentation where not);
          and making individuals comprehensible to the organization (by promoting their efforts and insuring that they
          stay connected and strategic).
        p.
          I believe in creating and maintaining alignment, where possible, between those activities that are fun,
          those that are fulfilling, and those that create value.
        //- Drudgery, like entropy, can’t be eliminated, but can be held at bay.
        //- blockquote
        //-   p.
        //-     If you want to build a ship, don't drum up people to collect wood and don't assign them tasks and work,
        //-     but rather teach them to long for the endless immensity of the sea.
        //-   .small Antoine de Saint-Exupery
        p.
          My favorite developers write code in order to figure out what to say
          as easily as they talk in order to figure out how to code.
          They understand both that a good meeting can prevent a month of wasted coding,
          and that a good line of code can prevent an hour of wasted meeting time.
          They understand that languages, platforms, management styles, and development methodologies
          all trade off between strengths and weaknesses, and are differently appropriate in different contexts.
        p. My favorite co-workers want to point at something and say “we did that!”, and want to have fun getting there.

      section#blog
        h2 Blog
        p.
          I published a <a href="http://blog.osteele.com">blog</a> from 2003 to 2008.
        p.
          Popular posts included
          <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2004/11/ides'>The <abbr>IDE</abbr> Divide</a> and
          <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2007/12/overloading-semicolon'>Overloading Semicolon</a>.
        p.
          Posts that failed to make a splash include
          <a href="http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2004/12/serving-clients">Service Clients</a> (an early attempt to describe <abbr>AJAX</abbr>), and
          <a href="http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2003/08/rethinking-mvc">Rethinking <abbr>MVC</abbr></a> (an early attempt to describe <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_View_ViewModel">MVVM</a>).
        p.
          The illustrations in my <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2008/05/my-git-workflow'>My Git Workflow</a>
          have been adapted (with permission) and improved many times. You can find better, and interactive, versions elsewhere on the web.

