        p You might also be here from a web search or link to:
        ul
          li.
            <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Dylan">Apple Dylan</a> was an attempt to make the concepts in Lisp applicable to application programming.
            Java, JavaScript, C#, and Objective C get 90% of the way there.
          li.
            <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QuickDraw_GX">Quickdraw GX</a> (Skia) and AlphaMask were early 2D graphics engines with configurable rendering pipelines.
            Cairo, Antigrain, and the (not-coincidentally-named) <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skia_Graphics_Engine">Skia Graphics Engine</a>
            are portable solutions today.
          li.
            <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenLaszlo">OpenLaszlo</a> introduced(?) constraint programming (aka <abbr>KVO</abbr>),
            data binding, and declarative components to application programming and to the web.
